			<hr noshade size="2">
			</p>
			<h3><img src="../../../images/blue-dot.gif">Technical View</h3>
			<dl>
				<dt><b>Satellite Datalink</b>
				<dd class="size2">We provide two satellite datalinks for this program. One is provided by JCSAT-1 which has a bandwidth of 2Mbps and uses WIDE JC driver for multicast link. The other is provided by JCSAT-3 with a bandwidth of 1.5Mbps, connectted between Japan and partners, Indonesia and Hong Kong. Details of this Network are shown in the following figures (planed).
				<p><img src="mito-ai3.gif"><br>
				</p>
				<p>The detail of the AI3-IX follows.</p>
				<p><img src="ai3-ix.gif"><br>
				</p>
				<dt><b>Applications</b>
				<dd>
				<ul>
					<li type="disc" class="size2"><b>Stream Works</b><br>
					Stream Works &quot;Encoder&quot; is located at Art Tower Mito. Video is distributed to several &quot;Network Server&quot; in Japan via JCSAT-1. Network Servers are placed at
					<ul>
						<li class="size2">Hibiya IWE Network Center (Tokyo)
						<li class="size2">Keio Univ. SFC (Fujisawa)
						<li class="size2">Kyusyu Univ.(Fukuoka)
						<li class="size2">AI3-IX (Nara)
					</ul>
					<p class="size2">We send data simultaneously by using IP multicast from the Encoder to the Network Servers, . The server at AI3-IX relays and delivers the broadcast to Stream Works clients in Indonesia and Hong-Kong via JCSAT-3.</p>
				</ul>
			</dl>
			<p>
			<hr noshade size="2">
			</p>
			<h3><img src="../../../images/blue-dot.gif">Issues in this experiment</h3>
			<ul>
				<li type="disc" class="size2">We have no StreamWorks redistribution servers in each connected AI3 partner side. In this case, AI3's satellite datalink will be used as the transport which will carry multimedia informations such as piano's realtime sounds and vision of the player Ryuichi Sakamoto using &quot;unicast&quot; approach.<br>
				<li type="disc" class="size2">The number of connection between server and clients must be hold under a limitted number since the bandwidth of the satellite datalink is only 1.5Mbps.
				<li type="disc" class="size2">Since RealAudio Server is only placed only at Mito this time, we cannot ensure enough quality for clients far away from Mito.
				<li type="disc" class="size2">At the begining of this project, we have planed to broadcast IP/TV inside Japan using multicast application such as <b>&quot;vic&quot;</b>, <b>&quot;vat&quot;</b>. However, since we have no enough stuffs and time for preparing the environments, this plan have been canceled.
			</ul>
			<p>
			<hr noshade size="2">
			</p>
			<h3><img src="../../../images/blue-dot.gif">Notes</h3>
			<ul>
				<li type="disc" class="size2">Mbone has not been constructed in AI3-NET yet. Thus, we cannot use &quot;multicast&quot; applications such as IP/TV to watch multimedia data within AI3-NET. It is nessesary to construct Mbone in AI3-NET if we want to use multicast application in the future.
				<li type="disc" class="size2">It is found that there are no enough bandwidth between IWE and AI3-IX connection for transmitting realtime stream. We consider to build more wide bandwidth AP(Access Point) in future.
				<li type="disc" class="size2">We only prepare redistribution server at Japan side of the AI3-NET for using multimedia application such as StreamWorks and RealAudio at this time. Thus it cause multiple application-specific unicast connections in the satellite datalink provided by JCSAT-3(1.5Mbps).
			</ul>
